# Plot
# Do selection
selection = alt.selection_single(fields=['continent'],name='Random')

# Do legend color and order
dom = ['Oceania', 'North America', 'Europe', 'South America', 'Asia', 'Africa']
rng = ['rgb(166, 216, 84)', 'rgb(231, 138, 195)', 'rgb(141, 160, 203)', 'rgb(255, 217, 47)', 'rgb(252, 141, 98)', 'rgb(102, 194, 165)']

# Plot bar plot
bar1=(alt.Chart(df2)
 .mark_bar()
 .encode(x='mean(Happiness Score):Q',
         y=alt.X('continent:N',
         sort=alt.EncodingSortField(field='Happiness Score', op='mean', 
                            order='descending')),
        # Set color
         color=alt.Color('continent', legend=alt.Legend(title="Continent"), scale=alt.
                    Scale(domain=dom, range=rng))
    
        # Write title
        ).properties(
                title={
                        "text":["Mean Happiness Score for Each Continent"]
                }
        )
).add_selection(selection)

# Change X and Y axis title
bar1.encoding.y.title = 'Continent'
bar1.encoding.x.title = 'Average Happiness Score'
bar1

# Do selection
selection = alt.selection_single(fields=['Country'],name='Random')

# Set color theme
color2 = alt.condition(selection,
                      alt.Color('Country:N', scale=alt.
                      Scale(scheme = 'set2')),
#                       alt.value('steelblue'),
                      alt.value('lightgray'))

# Plot bar plot
bar2=(alt.Chart(df1)
 .mark_bar()
 .encode(y='mean(Happiness Score):Q',
         x=alt.X('Country:N',
         sort=alt.EncodingSortField(field='Happiness Score', op='mean', 
                            order='descending')),
         color=color2
    
        # Add title and subtitle
        ).properties(
                title={
                        "text":["Mean Happiness Score in 12 Countries"],
                        "subtitle":["Two Countries from Each Continent"]
                }
        )
).add_selection(selection)

# Change X and Y axis title
bar2.encoding.x.title = 'Country Name'
bar2.encoding.y.title = 'Average Happiness Score'
bar2

# Set color theme
color2 = alt.condition(selection,
                      alt.Color('Country:N', scale=alt.
                      Scale(scheme = 'set2')),
#                       alt.value('steelblue'),
                      alt.value('lightgray'))

# Plot line plot
line1=(alt.Chart(df1)
 .mark_line()
 .encode(x=alt.X('year:O'),
         y=alt.Y('Happiness Score'),
         color=color2
        
        )
)

# Write title and X, Y axis title
line1.title ="Happiness Score for 12 Countries"
line1.encoding.x.title = 'Time (Year)'
line1.encoding.y.title = 'Happiness Score'
line1

fig1 = bar1
fig2 = bar2 | line1

# Show plot
bar2 | line1
